The association rules is a pattern which states that if one event occurs another event occurs with a certain probability.
It finds the relationship between otherwise unrelated data in a data resporitory.
Market Basket Analysis


           Support: The minimum times an item should be present in the frequent data set to be considered in the apriori algorithm
                     Eg: No of transaction with both beer and diaper / total number of transactions

           confidence: Basically the percentage of times a particular supplimentry product was bought along with a primary product

                       No of transactions when beer was bought when diaper was bought/ number of transactions in which diaper was bought

                      So the basic advantage of having such an analysis is that you need to promte only the primary product.
